Nigeria will discover their opponents in the 2023 Africa Cup of Nations qualifying series on April 19. This was confirmed by the Confederation of African Football (CAF) on Friday. CAF’s Organising Committee also approved modifications to the June 2022 window. The qualifiers begin in June 2022, with the final set of matches to be played in March, 2023. The Super Eagles were eliminated in the second round at the 2021 AFCON in Cameroon. The 2023 AFCON will take place in Cote d’Ivoire.